Ban said at a conference on Wednesday that he plans to meet with foreign ministers from five countries permanently present on the council - the US, Russia, China, England and France - on the sidelines of the General Assembly's ministerial session to discuss Syria.
Ban expressed regret that the divisions in the council and between the Syrian people and regional powers “made this situation unresolved.”
Ban called on the five permanent members to show the solidarity and unity shown when they managed to conclude an agreement on Iran’s nuclear weapons, thus addressing the crisis in Syria.
