Specifically, in the last 35 years, the market has grown sharply - by about 14 percent - heading towards an increase in the interest rate, quite invariably in the period of 250 days after (average rise of 2.6%) after which it returns to normal after 500 days, with an average return in the last six cycles of the Bar.
