According to the Georgia Anti-Poison Center, U.S. anti-poison centers have reported an increase of about 400% since 2010 in the number of children under the age of 12 who ingested high-alcohol hand detergent.
According to Dr. Gaylord Lopez, director of the Georgia Anti-Poison Center, ingestion of hand detergent in children under 12 years of age reported at anti-poison centers rose from 3,266 in 2010 to 16,117 in 2014.
