The government approved on Wednesday the "National Immigration Strategy for the period 2015-2018" and the "Action Plan for the current year", documents considered to be "another stage that Romania is going through in its efforts to modernize the process of managing immigration on the national territory", according to a press release.
The cited source shows that the strategy aims to effectively manage the phenomenon of immigration, including general strategic objectives, specific objectives and guidelines of action that reflect the policies established at European level, adapted to national realities.
In view of the problems faced by the states in the immediate vicinity of Romania, measures are considered for the unified and coherent management of situations caused by the possible emergence of an influx of illegal immigrants on the territory of Romania, generated by situations of crisis of a political, social, economic or military nature.
"Romanian authorities will contribute to the creation of a flexible admission system, but at the same time they will pay special attention to citizens from countries with migration potential or who may harm national security," the source added.
The strategy identifies a number of factors that can influence immigration and asylum, including maintaining the conflict situation in Syria, reactivating the conflict in Iraq, maintaining an unstable situation in the neighboring areas of Romania (Ukraine, Transnistria), perpetuating and increasing the intensity of the Israeli-Palestinian armed conflict.
On the other hand, the document also sets some general strategic objectives related to immigration, such as: promotion of legal migration, more stringent controls of the legality of the residence of third-country nationals on the territory of Romania and the appropriate application of removal measures and restrictive measures, improvement of the national asylum system.
The national strategy shall also include relevant specific objectives for the implementation and implementation of the overall strategic objectives.
These include: facilitating access to the territory of Romania for third-country nationals who meet the employment needs of the labour force, facilitating access of third-country nationals to higher education institutions in Romania for the areas and professions identified as deficient.
